  "commentary": "With SPX at 7092.11 trading above the 7072 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned as net long gamma and will mechanically sell into strength/buy weakness, creating stabilizing forces. The massive positive gamma walls at 7100 (+4952.9M) and 7200 (+7397.5M) should act as significant resistance levels where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while the negative gamma pocket at 7040 (-821.8M) represents a support zone where dealers would aggressively buy any dip. Key levels to watch are the 7072 flip strike as the regime boundary and the 7100/7200 gamma walls as upside magnets with increasing dealer resistance.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to grind higher toward 7100-7200 but with dealers providing selling pressure at those levels.",
